You can resolve this by simply removing the duplicate variables `factoryName`, `employeeAmount` and `producedAmount` from your `SteelFactory` class, otherwise the class will use the local variables that were never initialized instead of the correct variables from the super class. One big reason for extending a class is so that we don&#39;t have to re-use/re-type the same variables and methods in multiple classes.

Also, don&#39;t forget to use `@Override` annotation, it helps you keep track of which methods have been extended and [helps prevent common mistakes][1].

